  "question": "Marissa is hiking a 12-mile trail. She took 1 hour to walk the first 4 miles, then another hour to walk the next two miles. If she wants her average speed to be 4 miles per hour, what speed (in miles per hour) does she need to walk the remaining distance?",
  "prompt": "Marissa is hiking a 12-mile trail. She took 1 hour to walk the first 4 miles, then another hour to walk the next two miles. If she wants her average speed to be 4 miles per hour, what speed (in miles per hour) does she need to walk the remaining distance?\n\nShow your work briefly and put the final answer in \\boxed{}.",
  "gold_answer": "6",
  "generated_text": "To find the required speed for the remaining distance, we need to determine the total time Marissa has available and the distance she needs to cover.\n\n1.  **Calculate the total distance:**\n    The total trail length is $12$ miles.\n    The first part of the trail is $4$ miles.\n    The second part of the trail is $2$ miles.\n    Distance remaining = Total distance - (Distance of first part + Distance of second part)\n    Distance remaining = $12 - (4 + 2) = 12 - 6 = 6$ miles.\n\n2.  **Calculate the total time available:**\n    The problem states she took $1$ hour for the first part and $1$ hour for the second part.\n    Total time spent so far = $1 + 1 = 2$ hours.\n\n3.  **Set up the equation for average speed:**\n    The formula for average speed is $\\text{Average Speed} = \\frac{\\text{Total Distance}}{\\text{Total Time}}$.\n    We want the average speed to be $4$ mph.\n    Let $v$ be the speed for the remaining 6 miles.\n    Time taken for the remaining distance = $\\frac{\\text{Distance remaining}}{v} = \\frac{6}{v}$ hours.\n\n    The equation for the new average speed is:\n    $$ \\frac{\\text{Total Distance}}{\\text{Total Time}} = \\text{Average Speed} $$\n    $$ \\frac{12}{2 + \\frac{6}{v}} = 4 $$\n\n4.  **Solve for $v$:**\n    Multiply both sides by the denominator:\n    $$ 12 = 4 \\left( 2 + \\frac{6}{v} \\right) $$\n    Divide both sides by 4:\n    $$ 3 = 2 + \\frac{6}{v} $$\n    Subtract 2 from both sides:\n    $$ 1 = \\frac{6}{v} $$\n    Multiply both sides by $v$:\n    $$ v = 6 $$\n\nMarissa needs to walk the remaining 6 miles at a speed of 6 miles per hour.\n\n\\boxed{6}\n",
  "pred_answer": "6",
